column4: (Teaching Effectiveness)   1. Your teacher explains concepts clearly and provides easy-to-follow instructions.
column5: (Teaching Effectiveness) 2. Your teacher connects lessons to real life situations (IK) and CI, C+, and UNSDGs.
column6: (Teaching Effectiveness) 3. Your teacher encourages critical thinking questions during lessons.
column7: (Teaching Effectiveness) 4. Your teacher utilizes technology (smart boards), hands-on activities, and teaching aids to enhance interactivity.
column8: (Teaching Effectiveness) 5. Your teacher is always punctual to classes and off classes.
column9: (Classroom Management)  1. Your teacher manages disruptions effectively.
column10: (Classroom Management) 2. Your teacher creates respectful and positive classroom environment.
column11: (Classroom Management) 3. Your teacher treats all students fairly.
column12: (Classroom Management) 4. Your teacher provides timely and constructive feedback.
column13: (Classroom Management) 5. The assessments reflect the topics taught in class.
column14: (Classroom Management) 6. Your teacher allows opportunities to improve your performance (e.g. re test, extra assignments, ….).
column15: (Student Engagement )  1. Your teacher encourages active participation in class (group work, discussions, etc.).
column16: (Student Engagement ) 2. Your teacher recognizes and values student contributions.
column17: (Student Engagement ) 3. Your teacher motivates you to do your best.
column18: (Student Engagement ) 4. Your teacher makes learning enjoyable and attractive.
column19: (Communication      & Support)  1. The teacher explains assignments and expectations clearly.
column20: (Communication      & Support) 2. Your teacher listens to your questions and concerns.
column21: (Communication      & Support) 3. your teacher provides extra help when you need it.
